{"body": "I'm not sure about this one. If you know in advance that the delegation target might be `nil` and you rescue that exception, then this is not really an exceptional case and you are writing control flow with exceptions. Why not simply define the delegation method yourself and handle the case explicitly?\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ndef name\r\n  if @target\r\n    @target.name\r\n  else\r\n    # .. code that would otherwise reside in the `rescue` part\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/19495753", "created_at": "2013-06-15T12:29:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10828#issuecomment-19495753", "updated_at": "2013-06-15T12:29:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10828, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/senny", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fd1359f9934ee5a75ed441ffce412a0a1.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3d698e2872c07061a455d9e250861235", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "senny", "type": "User", "id": 5402, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/senny/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523cacfabd354364b9002197"}, "id": 19495753, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10828"}
